In [19]:
import pandas as pd
In [20]:
data = pd.read_csv('data.csv')
ids = data['Responder_id']
lang = data['LanguagesWorkedWith']
    
language_counter = Counter()

for r in lang:
    language_counter.update(r.split(';'))
    
for x in language_counter.most_common(15):
    languages.append(x[0])
    popularity.append(x[1])
    
languages.reverse()
popularity.reverse()

In [24]:
data = pd.read_csv('Dev.csv')
ages = data['Age']
dev_salaries = data['All_Devs']
py_salaries = data['Python']
js_salaries = data['JavaScript']
fig=plt.figure(figsize=(16, 9), dpi= 300)


plt.plot(ages, dev_salaries, color='#444444',
         linestyle='--', label='All Devs')

plt.plot(ages, py_salaries, label='Python')

overall_median = 57287

plt.fill_between(ages, py_salaries, dev_salaries,
                 where=(py_salaries > dev_salaries),
                 interpolate=True, alpha=0.25, label='Above Avg')

plt.fill_between(ages, py_salaries, dev_salaries,
                 where=(py_salaries <= dev_salaries),
                 interpolate=True, color='red', alpha=0.25, label='Below Avg')

plt.legend()

plt.title('Median Salary (USD) by Age')
plt.xlabel('Ages')
plt.ylabel('Median Salary (USD)')

plt.tight_layout()

plt.show()

import random

def random_mul(x):
    return x * random.random() *10

x = [random.random()*random.random()*10 for i in range(100)]
y = list(map(random_mul,x))
color = [random.randint(0,10) for i in range(100)]
sizes = [random.randint(0,200) for i in range(100)]

x_values=[]
y_values=[]

index = count()

def animate(i):
    x_values.append(index)
    y_values.append(random.randint(0,10))
    
    plt.plot(x_values,y_values)
    
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(16,9),dpi=300)
ani = FuncAnimation(plt.gcf(),animate,interval = 1000)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
